               file.


          ----llll   CONTROL-L will not be treated as a special character.
               By default, a CONTROL-L causes the --More-- prompt to
               be displayed immediately, just as though the end of the
               current page had been reached.


          ----ssss   When specified, duplicate blank lines are not
               displayed. For example, if a file contains three blank
               lines in a row, only one blank line will be displayed.
               This is useful for looking at documents that are
               formatted for printing and have multiple blank lines at
               the top and bottom of each page.


          ----uuuu   Normally _m_o_r_e displays text that is underlined in
               reverse video.  This option disables this translation.


          ----rrrr   This option causes control characters to be displayed
               as a caret ("^") and a letter.  For example, CONTROL-C
               would be displayed as ^C.  By default, _m_o_r_e ignores
               non-carriage control characters.


          ----wwww   A warning message will be displayed when all files have
               been displayed and _m_o_r_e is about to exit.  This is
               useful when _m_o_r_e is invoked from another program or
               batch file that might clear the screen before the
               contents can be read.  The prompt "--No More--" waits
               for the user to press a key before _m_o_r_e exits.


          ----!!!!   Causes _m_o_r_e to ignore any default settings that are
